Currently, there is no `??` operator in javascript.

You can use the [ternary][1] operator:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    var x = undefined; 
    console.log(x == undefined ? &#39;default&#39; : x);

